<h1 id="set-up-hub-accessorial-charges-and-accessorial-masters">Set up hub accessorial charges and accessorial masters</h1>


<p>This procedure shows how to create an accessorial master for a hub and use that master to create a hub accessorial charge. The procedure uses the USMF dataset. This set up will typically be done by a transportation coordinator.</p>
<h2 id="set-up-a-hub-master">Set up a hub master</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Transportation management &gt; Setup &gt; Rating &gt; Accessorial masters.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Accessorial master field, type a value.</li>
<li>In the Name field, type a value.</li>
<li>In the Accessorial type field, select 'Hub'.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
<li>Close the page.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-up-a-hub-accessorial-charge">Set up a hub accessorial charge</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Transportation management &gt; Setup &gt; Rating &gt; Hub accessorial charges.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Hub accessorial ID field, type a value.</li>
<li>In the Hub field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.</li>
<li>In the Hub position field, select an option.
<ul>
<li>You can either create the charge as a pickup or drop-off. Depending on your selection the charge will be applied to the corresponding transportation segment on your route.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>In the Accessorial master field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.
<ul>
<li>Select the master you just created.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
<li>Close the page.</li>
</ol>
